comments.body:
In 5a1233c0:

Small idea: what about having an always increasing `lock_time` number?. It will ensure different tx ids and let you remove the `unique_set_num` as well as the fast RNG for the prevout hash which doesn't seems to be used anywhere.

E.g.
```c++
static BlockTxns CreateRandomTransactions(size_t num_txns)
{
    static uint32_t next_locktime{0};

    BlockTxns txns;
    txns.reserve(num_txns);
    // Simplest spk for every tx
    CScript spk = CScript() << OP_TRUE;
    for (uint32_t i = 0; i < num_txns; ++i) {
        CMutableTransaction tx;
        tx.vin.resize(1);
        tx.vout.resize(1);
        tx.vout.emplace_back(CTxOut{CENT, spk});
        tx.nLockTime = next_locktime++;
        txns.emplace_back(MakeTransactionRef(tx));
    }
    return txns;
}
```

